			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64632987"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64632987">I take it to mean <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AI_accelerator" title="wikipedia.org">AI accelerators<span class="substr"> </span></a> [wikipedia.org] or NPUs that must be baked into the silicon and the APIs that must be created/maintained to call AI functions. Chip design is always a balance about what is included in the design in terms of need vs cost. For example, a chip for a streaming box may have AV decoding functions in the hardware but not encoding functions. A chip used for a home router may not need any decoding circuitry but may have specialized network routing functions. As with all things, if would cost more</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64632987">

